com.percussion.extension
Interface IPSAssemblyLocation

All Superinterfaces:
IPSExtension
All Known Implementing Classes:
PSConcatAssemblyLocation, PSConcatWithIdAssemblyLocation, PSDefaultAssemblyLocation, PSGenericAssembly
public interface IPSAssemblyLocation
extends IPSExtension

This interface specifies the functionality to be implemented by all content assembler location generators. The implementing classes should not be called directly, instead they will be called from the PSGeneratePubLocation for the current context and contenttype.

Method Detail

createLocation

String createLocation(Object[] params,
                      IPSRequestContext request)
                      throws PSExtensionException
This method creates a new publishing location string for the provided parameters.

Parameters:
params - an array of parameters as specified in the RXLOCATIONSCHEME table for the current context and contenttype, nut null, might be empty.
request - the request for which the location needs to be created, not null.
Throws:
PSExtensionException - to report any error in the execution of the implementing class.
